A hollowed out skull containing a dark and somewhat strong smelling liquid. It's the specialty drink at the Salty Dog Tavern.
Robes of the Order of Light +1

The Shining Hand Monastery in Vaasa has made an impressive reputation, and a small fortune, designing these robes. Demand has spread across many nations, such that different variations on the similar robes keep the monks hard at work. The robes increase a monks senses to such a degree that she can focus on her opponent and move her body to absorb blows. One drawback to these robes is that they make the wearer supersensitive to noise. Even in the quiet rooms of the monastery the wearer would have a hard time distinguishing between the snoring of a brother down the hall and the scuttling of a rat under his bed.

Former Royal Magician Vangerdahast to King Azoun IV of Cormyr was once an accomplished adventurer of high fame. One reason he became popular in wizardly circles was his creation of the Adventurer's Robe. Mages have always struggled with the limitations placed on them by the ability to cast arcane magics. These robes give the mage an edge in surviving encounters with melee fighters by being able to absorb some damage from hits.

This is a volume 1 of armorcrafting recipes.

As you flip through the pages of this book, you see the recipes of four different types of armor and the process of how to make each one described in full.
Recipes --------------
*Scale Mail* 6 - Ingots of any kind 1 - Cured Medium Leather Hide
*Chain Shirt* 8 - Ingots of any kind 1 - Cloth Padding
*Chainmail* 16 - Ingots of any kind 2 - Cloth Padding
*Breastplate* 22 - Ingots of any kind 1 - Crafted Studded Leather Armor
This is a volume 2 of armorcrafting recipes.

As you flip through the pages of this book, you see the recipes of four different types of armor and the process of how to make each one described in full.
Recipes --------------
*Splint Mail* 16 - Ingots of any kind 2 - Cured Large Leather Hide 3 - Cloth Padding
*Banded Mail* 20 - Ingots of any kind 2 - Tanned Large Leather Hide 3 - Cloth Padding
*Half-Plate* 28 - Ingots of any kind 1 - Crafted Chainmail Armor of the same metal
*Full-Plate* 40 - Ingots of any kind 2 - Hardened Large Leather Hide

Weaponcrafting usually uses less components than armorcrafting so it is cheaper to master. Although you may not make as much money with it as armocrafting, you will eventually be able to make some powerful weapons when you start imbueing and adding jewels.
Recipes -------------- Axes: *Hand Axe* - 4 Ingots
Bladed Weapons: *Dagger* - 2 Ingots *Longsword* - 6 Ingots
Blunt Weapons: *Mace* - 3 Ingots
Exotic: *Kama* - 2 Ingots
Tools: *Smithing Hammer* - 4 Ingots *Pickaxe* - 5 Ingots *Skinning Knife* - 3 Ingots
**Be warned that tools are harder to make because they use up more ingots on failures than other items**
